@node features "Features"
@prev features
@next requirements
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Features of DirSize@{uu}@{ub}

   Writing of this tool was heavily inspired by DirSize command written by
   Steve Robb (util/cli/DirSize.lha). But since it was not capable handle
   big (4+ gig) directories correctly I created new one my own.


   · can display results in bytes, kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes and terabytes

   · can handle large directories using 64 bit math

   · numbers are displayed in localized form, including the decimal point :-)

   · find size of multiple directories according to an AmigaDOS pattern

   · include only files matching a certain AmigaDOS pattern

   · accumulate number of files and directories

   · sort results by path, size or number of dirs/files
@endnode
@node requirements "Requirements"
@prev features
@next usage
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Requirements for DirSize@{uu}@{ub}

   Minimum requirements for @{b}DirSize@{ub} Amiga version are

   Kickstart 3.0
   MC68020


   Minimum requirements for @{b}DirSize@{ub} MorphOS version are

   MorphOS 1.0
@endnode
@node usage "Usage"
@prev requirements
@next keyword_dir
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Usage of DirSize@{uu}@{ub}

   @{b}DirSize@{ub} is a CLI only tool. The command line template of @{b}DirSize@{ub} is as follows:
 
   DIR/M,P=PATTERN/K,B=BYTES/S,KB=KILOBYTES/S,MB=MEGABYTES/S,GB=GIGABYTES/S,TB=TERABYTES/S,
   NOERRORS/S,SORT/K:

   If you have any experience of AmigaDOS templates, many should be self-explanatory.

   @{" DIR/M             " link keyword_dir}
   @{" P=PATTERN/K       " link keyword_pattern}
   @{" B=BYTES/S         " link keyword_sizetype}
   @{" KB=KILOBYTES/S    " link keyword_sizetype}
   @{" MB=MEGABYTES/S    " link keyword_sizetype}
   @{" GB=GIGABYTES/S    " link keyword_sizetype}
   @{" TB=TERABYTES/S    " link keyword_sizetype}
   @{" NOERRORS/S        " link keyword_noerrors}
   @{" SORT/K            " link keyword_sort}

   Once each directory has been scanned, the program will output the size  of
   the directory together with the number of files and sub-directories inside
   it.

   Starting from version 2.6 DirSize supports 64bit DOS. Currently it only works
   in MorphOS 2.0 or newer.
@endnode
@node keyword_dir "DIR/M"
@prev usage
@next keyword_pattern
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Keyword: DIR/M@{uu}@{ub}

   Specify the directories you wish to count. If none are given, then the
   current directory is used. You can also use pattern matching to include
   or exclude certain directories:

   @{b}DirSize HD0:#?@{ub}

   This scans every directory in HD0: separately. It is far different from:

   @{b}DirSize HD0:@{ub}

   In this case you get the total size of HD0:.
@endnode
@node keyword_pattern "P=PATTERN/K"
@prev keyword_dir
@next keyword_sizetype
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Keyword: P=PATTERN/K@{uu}@{ub}

   You can also include and exlude files which match the given AmigaDOS pattern.

   For example if you want count all .info files just type:

   @{b}DirSize HD0: PATTERN=#?.info@{ub}


   The default is include all files.
@endnode
@node keyword_sizetype "B=BYTES/S,KB=KILOBYTES/S,MB=MEGABYTES/S,GB=GIGABYTES/S,AUTO/S"
@prev keyword_pattern
@next keyword_noerrors
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Keywords: B=BYTES/S,KB=KILOBYTES/S,MB=MEGABYTES/S,GB=GIGABYTES/S,TB=TERABYTES/S@{uu}@{ub}

   By the default @{b}DirSize@{ub} selects a suitable unit for each directory but you can
   can also pick one from command line.
@endnode
@node keyword_noerrors
@prev keyword_sizetype
@next keyword_sort
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Keyword: NOERRORS/S@{uu}@{ub}

   Specifying this keywords prevent @{b}DirSize@{ub} to stop directory scanning
   in case of any DOS error.
@endnode
@node keyword_sort
@prev keyword_noerrors
@next author
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}Keyword: SORT/K@{uu}@{ub}

   You can sort the ouput according to one of several fields. To specify
   which field, use one of the following keywords:

   @{u}Keyword@{uu}  @{u}Action@{uu}
   NONE     No sorting (default)
   PATH     Sort according to the names of directories
   SIZE     Sort according to the size of directories
   FILES    Sort according to the number of files in directories
   DIRS     Sort according to the number of sub-directories

   If sorting is by SIZE, FILES or DIR, you will not see any output until all specified
   directories have been scanned.

   An example:

   @{b}DirSize MODS:#? SORT=PATH@{ub}
@endnode
@node history "Program History"
@prev keyword_sort
@next author
@toc  main

   @{b}@{u}History of DirSize@{uu}@{ub}

   Version 2.6 (24.9.2008)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - Added support for 64bit directory scan (MorphOS 2.0 or newer)


   Version 2.5 (20.6.2006)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - Fixed errors with 64bit printing (%lld was accidentally used in
        Amiga version)
      - Fixed MorphOS version to print size right (rounding error)
      - Thanks to all who reported those bugs!


   Version 2.4 (25.1.2006)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - Fixed Amiga version to calculate 64bit integers properly
      - Fixed MorphOS version to not return error code 20 on success


   Version 2.3 (19.5.2003)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - Decimals were not ok. Fixed.
      - Handles multiple directories now (DIR/M)

      - Added SORT keyword
      - Added small guide
      - Fixed softlink handling


   Version 2.2 (7.12.2002)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - Added NOERRORS keyword (ignores all errors during scan)
      - Fixed stupid error causing enforcer hits in some cases

      - More options should be added


   Version 2.1 (2.10.2002)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - Added PATTERN keyword
      - Added BYTES, KILOBYTES, MEGABYTES, GIGABYTES and TERABYTES keywords
      - Fixed minor bug with IoErr()

      - Terabytes are supported now


   Version 2.0 (18.9.2002)
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      - first working version
@endnode
